# Groups

- 80,000 Hours seems to have [very accessible research](https://80000hours.org/topic/causes/meta-causes/global-priorities-research/) available.
- [Copenhagen Consensus Center](http://www.copenhagenconsensus.com/)
- The [Open Philanthropy Project]() ([cause reports](http://www.openphilanthropy.org/research/cause-reports)) (formerly GiveWell labs)
    - See also certain posts on the GiveWell blog like [this one on US policy](http://blog.givewell.org/2014/05/29/potential-u-s-policy-focus-areas/) ([this spreadsheet](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1b4Nr7wOUWpkjGkn5WLeHZBcpTub3f3y5qAbppuAJ_Ts) contains a full list of causes in this area GiveWell has investigated or hopes to investigate).
Alexander Berger(?)'s [back-of-the-envelope calculations](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1DTl4TYaTPMAtwQTju9PZmxKhZTCh6nmi-Vh8cnSgYak) also contain a lot of information.
- The [Global Priorities Project](http://www.fhi.ox.ac.uk/research/global-priorities-project/)
- Arguably [Foundational Research Institute](http://foundational-research.org/)
- The [Cause Prioritization Wiki](http://causeprioritization.org) (this wiki)
- The [Good Technology Project](http://goodtechnologyproject.org/about/), focusing on technology.
It has [announced to EAF](http://effective-altruism.com/ea/sa/announcing_the_good_technology_project/).
- The [Oxford Prioritisation Project]()
- The [Global Priorities Institute]()
- Forethought Foundation for Global Priorities Research
- Some subset of the Centre for Effective Altruism
- [Long-Term World Improvement]() (not a very coordinated effort, but the group discusses a variety of causes and intriguing ways to improve the future)
- [Priority Wiki]()
- UN General Assembly Open Working Group on Sustainable Development Goals[^un]
- [Founders Pledge](https://founderspledge.com/research)
- Future of Humanity Institute

